      "byte_end": 706
    },
    {
      "id": "block_7",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Basic examples",
      "raw_len": 14,
      "placeholder": "@@text:63:831783@@",
      "byte_start": 774,
      "byte_end": 788
    },
    {
      "id": "block_8",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Uniform flow",
      "raw_len": 12,
      "placeholder": "@@text:62:2473cb@@",
      "byte_start": 865,
      "byte_end": 877
    },
    {
      "id": "block_9",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "The complex potential\n                    @@math:8:8c26cf@@\n                    corresponds to uniform flow at speed @@math:19:56f399@@ in a direction making an angle\n                    with the @@math:20:cfd0cd@@-axis.\n                ",
      "raw_len": 237,
      "placeholder": "@@text:61:a88b3e@@",
      "byte_start": 903,
      "byte_end": 1140
    },
    {
      "id": "block_10",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Here we are interested in finding the velocity field @@math:18:29972c@@\n                    But first we need to obtain the stream function @@math:21:ddf3ba@@ which is the\n                    imaginary component of (@@math:22:a744cc@@). ",
      "raw_len": 237,
      "placeholder": "@@text:60:8ab902@@",
      "byte_start": 1165,
      "byte_end": 1402
    },
    {
      "id": "block_11",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Rewriting (@@math:23:e2a66a@@)\n                    we obtain\n                    @@math:9:8eff4f@@\n                    Thus\n                    @@math:10:0f76c5@@\n                ",
      "raw_len": 179,
      "placeholder": "@@text:59:145f98@@",
      "byte_start": 1428,
      "byte_end": 1607
    },
    {
      "id": "block_12",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Finally, since @@math:24:14d8ca@@ and\n                    @@math:25:669c25@@\n                    we have that\n                    @@math:11:6e10fe@@\n                ",
      "raw_len": 165,
      "placeholder": "@@text:58:0a3487@@",
      "byte_start": 1633,
      "byte_end": 1798
    },
    {
      "id": "block_13",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "The applet below shows a simulation of the uniform flow. Drag the sliders to\n                    change parameters. Click on [[code]]Trace[[/code]] button to show streamlines. Click on\n                    [[code]]Field[[/code]] button to show vector field.\n                ",
      "raw_len": 265,
      "placeholder": "@@text:57:196990@@",
      "byte_start": 1823,
      "byte_end": 2088
    },
    {
      "id": "block_14",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Stagnation point flow",
      "raw_len": 21,
      "placeholder": "@@text:56:5d2e0b@@",
      "byte_start": 2792,
      "byte_end": 2813
    },
    {
      "id": "block_15",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "The complex potential\n                    @@math:12:1c5681@@\n                    corresponds to the stagnation point flow with strength @@math:26:6672da@@\n                ",
      "raw_len": 171,
      "placeholder": "@@text:55:76628c@@",
      "byte_start": 2839,
      "byte_end": 3010
    },
    {
      "id": "block_16",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Source &amp; Sink",
      "raw_len": 17,
      "placeholder": "@@text:54:2a17e4@@",
      "byte_start": 3695,
      "byte_end": 3712
    },
    {
      "id": "block_17",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "A source of strength @@math:27:7ac897@@ at the origin is represented\n                    by the complex potential\n                    @@math:13:a96cc2@@\n                    Note that this is a multi-valued function, with a branch point\n                    at the origin. If @@math:28:992954@@ then the complex potential corresponds to a sink.\n                ",
      "raw_len": 359,
      "placeholder": "@@text:53:c253f0@@",
      "byte_start": 3738,
      "byte_end": 4097
    },
    {
      "id": "block_18",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "It is easy to generalize (\\ref{source-sink}) for an arbitrary point @@math:29:369c99@@ in the complex\n                    plane. The required complex potential is\n                    @@math:14:6c98d4@@\n                    where @@math:30:3d0be4@@\n                ",
      "raw_len": 263,
      "placeholder": "@@text:52:fd5a1f@@",
      "byte_start": 4751,
      "byte_end": 5014
    },
    {
      "id": "block_19",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Vortex",
      "raw_len": 6,
      "placeholder": "@@text:51:7c3b5f@@",
      "byte_start": 5110,
      "byte_end": 5116
    },
    {
      "id": "block_20",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "A vortex of strength @@math:31:7cab4e@@ at the origin is represented\n                    by the complex potential\n                    @@math:15:e7dc79@@\n                    This is again a multi-valued function. For @@math:32:0e0b2c@@ rotation is anticlockwise,\n                    and for @@math:33:c2ba56@@ rotation is clockwise.\n                ",
      "raw_len": 348,
      "placeholder": "@@text:50:a83335@@",
      "byte_start": 5142,
      "byte_end": 5490
    },
    {
      "id": "block_21",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "A vortex at an arbitrary point @@math:34:79e292@@ is represented by the\n                    complex potential\n                    @@math:16:79cc9a@@\n                    where @@math:35:0ae00c@@\n                ",
      "raw_len": 210,
      "placeholder": "@@text:49:d3c46d@@",
      "byte_start": 6119,
      "byte_end": 6329
    },
    {
      "id": "block_22",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "[[strong]]Exercise:[[/strong]] Find the velocity fields of the Stagnation point,\n                        Source &amp; Sink and Vortex flows.",
      "raw_len": 136,
      "placeholder": "@@text:48:04f913@@",
      "byte_start": 6398,
      "byte_end": 6534
    },
    {
      "id": "block_23",
      "tag": "h2",
      "text": "Combining complex potentials",
      "raw_len": 28,
      "placeholder": "@@text:47:25a2e3@@",
      "byte_start": 6653,
      "byte_end": 6681
    },
    {
      "id": "block_24",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "\n                    The basic flows presented above can be combined by simply superimposing the corresponding\n                    complex potentials.",
      "raw_len": 150,
      "placeholder": "@@text:46:6d49b3@@",
      "byte_start": 6706,
      "byte_end": 6856
    },
    {
      "id": "block_25",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "For example, consider a uniform flow @@math:36:231a7d@@ with speed @@math:37:87fa40@@ and a source\n                    @@math:38:e3e3b9@@ with @@math:39:2d4e6d@@ Thus we can produce the complex potential\n                    @@math:17:a53fb7@@\n                    The following applet shows the flow produced by (\\ref{comb}). Drag the sliders to\n                    change parameters.",
      "raw_len": 383,
      "placeholder": "@@text:45:ad36a3@@",
      "byte_start": 6881,
      "byte_end": 7264
    },
    {
      "id": "block_26",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "[[strong]]Exercise:[[/strong]] Find the velocity field of the flow produced\n                        by a source of strength @@math:40:3cbc5a@@ in a uniform flow at speed @@math:41:f67ade@@ in the\n                        @@math:42:114ae0@@-direction.",
      "raw_len": 245,
      "placeholder": "@@text:44:f5d067@@",
      "byte_start": 7967,
      "byte_end": 8212
    },
    {
      "id": "block_27",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Uniform flow around circle [[i class=\"fa-solid fa-angles-right\"]][[/i]]",
      "raw_len": 67,
      "placeholder": "@@text:43:0e2a54@@",
      "byte_start": 8417,
      "byte_end": 8484
    }
